6 March 2013President Jacob Zuma delivered the State of the Nation Address (SoNA) on Thursday, 14 February 2013 where he outlined government s priorities and plans and set the tone for delivery in the year ahead.Members of the media are invited to the post SoNA media briefing on Infrastructure Development and Job Creation. In attendance will be the Ministers of Trade &amp; Industry, Dr Rob Davies; Labour, Ms. Mildred Oliphant and Transport, Mr Ben Martins.The briefing will take place as follows:Date: Thursday, 7 March 2013 Time: 11h00 Venue: Imbizo Media Centre in Parliament, Cape TownNB: There will be a video-link to the GCIS Auditorium, 1st Floor, Midtown Building, Pretoria. Kindly confirm attendance by email or sms to: Tshegofatso Modubu (Pretoria) E-mail: tshegofatso@gcis.gov.za Cell: 083 276 0786Loedfie Hendricks (Cape Town) E-mail: loedfieh@gcis.gov.za Cell: 082 670 4145Enquiries: Pheliswa Sebati (Pretoria) Cell: 082 413 4609Liezil Cerf (Cape Town) Cell: 076 778 2380Issued by: Government Communication and Information System (GCIS)